{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3fd0a2cf-5e65-4c66-97f4-09197a9f6f2e","content":"The issue is classic F# file ordering. In the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed **before** `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed earlier.\n\n**Fix:** Reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_SGptMMZ7ONXeHWqTC6XiTf","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1388e92271e549fd9dd050516984c283/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1388e92271e549fd9dd050516984c283/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"885f7ea5-f0e5-4682-b31b-37e83fde8002","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs — depends on Domain.fs (opens BrokenOrder.Domain)\n2. Domain.fs — defines the types\n3. Program.fs — depends on both\n\nServices.fs is listed before Domain.fs, but Services.fs depends on Domain.fs. The fix is to put Domain.fs first.","outputTokens":397,"requestId":"5C18:21AE1A:5EBE6A6:678B32D:69F15600"},"id":"c890f7ed-b81f-4827-aa5d-21ee13c00591","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:20.802Z","parentId":"dc96c760-ed88-4e60-a3f4-f486f48cf100"}
